<p>Sadly, it will pass easily, because it DIRECTLY affects only a tiny portion of the population. It takes only a simple majority to become part of the California constitution. LATER it will affect everyone as the aging rich abandon the Golden State.</p>
<p>But few will connect the dots &#8212; let alone connect the dots prior to the implementation of this huge &#8220;soak the rich&#8221; tax&#8221; &#8212; a new tax on top of by FAR the nation&#8217;s highest state income tax.</p>
<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-133868' data-commentid="133868" data-postid="94012" data-belowelement="comment-133868" data-respondelement="respond" aria-label='Reply to Richard Rider'><i class="fa fa-reply left"></i>Reply this comment</a> </div>
